2
3 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 23-115-103(21), concerning the definition of
4 "net proceeds" under the Arkansas Scholarship Lottery Act, is amended to read
5 as follows:
6 (21)(A) “Net proceeds” means lottery proceeds less:
7 (A)(i) Operating expenses;
8 (B)(ii) The amount of fidelity fund revenue under § 23-115-603
9 that exceeds is required to increase the fidelity fund to five hundred
10 thousand dollars ($500,000);
11 (C)(iii) The undepreciated amount of capital assets; and amount
12 of any adjustments required for Multi-State Lottery Association reserves to
13 meet the Multi-State Lottery Association reserve requirements; and
14 (iv) The amount of any accrual or other accounting
15 adjustment that will result in a debit or credit balance in the Office of the
16 Arkansas Lottery's Unrestricted Net Position account, except for any
17 restricted net position account.
18 (D) Accruals that will not result in a cash outflow;
19 (B) "Net proceeds" includes fidelity fund revenue that
20 exceeds a fidelity fund balance of five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000).
21 (C) "Net proceeds" shall be based on generally accepted
22 accounting principles in accordance with § 23-115-206(a)(6);
23
24 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 23-115-103(23)(I), concerning payments to
25 the Division of Higher Education as a cost under the definition of "operating
26 expenses" under the Arkansas Scholarship Lottery Act, is repealed.
27 (I) Payments to the Division of Higher Education to:
28 (i) Reimburse the division for the costs of
29 administering scholarship awards funded with net proceeds; and
30 (ii) Replenish nonlottery state educational
31 resources expended by the division on scholarship awards otherwise funded
32 with net proceeds;
33
