34 SECTION 13. Arkansas Code § 23-115-802 is repealed.
35 23-115-802. Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account.
36 (a) The Office of the Arkansas Lottery shall maintain a Scholarship
5 03-18-2025 14:03:49 CRH049

As Engrossed: S2/25/25 S3/11/25 S3/18/25 SB232
1 Shortfall Reserve Trust Account.
2 (b)(1) An amount equal to four percent (4%) of the total amount of net
3 proceeds disbursed during the preceding fiscal year in the form of
4 scholarships and grants for higher education shall be deposited from lottery
5 proceeds each year until the amount in the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve
6 Trust Account equals twenty million dollars ($20,000,000).
7 (2) Thereafter, only the amount necessary to maintain the
8 Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account in an amount equal to twenty
9 million dollars ($20,000,000) shall be deposited into the Scholarship
10 Shortfall Reserve Trust Account.
11 (3) Any amount in the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust
12 Account exceeding twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) shall be considered
13 net proceeds and shall be deposited annually into one (1) or more trust
14 accounts at one (1) or more financial institutions by July 1 of each year.
15 (c)(1)(A) Except as provided in subdivision (c)(2) of this section, if
16 net proceeds in any year are not sufficient to meet the amount allocated for
17 scholarships under the Arkansas Academic Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-
18 85-201 et seq., the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account may be drawn
19 upon to meet the deficiency according to the procedural requirements
20 established under subdivision (c)(3)(B) of this section.
21 (B) In the event that the funding available in the
22 Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account is not sufficient to meet the
23 remaining amount allocated for scholarships funded with net proceeds from the
24 state lottery, up to the first twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) of funds
25 allocated in the Higher Education Grants Fund Account may be drawn upon to
26 meet the deficiency.
27 (2) Except as provided in subdivision (c)(3)(B) of this section,
28 the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account shall not be drawn upon to
29 fund Arkansas Workforce Challenge Scholarships under the Arkansas Workforce
30 Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-301 et seq., Arkansas Concurrent
31 Challenge Scholarships under the Arkansas Concurrent Challenge Scholarship
32 Program, § 6-85-401 et seq., or any other scholarship funded with net
33 proceeds from the state lottery.
34 (3)(A) Determining the maximum amount of loans from the
35 Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account to the Arkansas Academic
36 Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-201 et seq., the Arkansas Workforce
6 03-18-2025 14:03:49 CRH049

As Engrossed: S2/25/25 S3/11/25 S3/18/25 SB232
1 Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-301 et seq., or the Arkansas Concurrent
2 Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-401 et seq., is the prerogative of the
3 General Assembly. This is usually accomplished by the General Assembly's
4 delineating such funding allocations for the various scholarship programs,
5 with the approval of the Administrative Rules Subcommittee of the Legislative
6 Council and through oversight as required by law by the Lottery Oversight
7 Subcommittee of the Legislative Council. Further, the General Assembly
8 determines that the Division of Higher Education may operate more efficiently
9 with some flexibility, therefore it is both necessary and appropriate that
10 the General Assembly maintain oversight by requiring prior approval of the
11 Legislative Council or the Joint Budget Committee as provided by this
12 section.
13 (B) If the division determines it is necessary to borrow
14 from the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust Account to fund scholarships
15 under the Arkansas Academic Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-201 et
16 seq., the Arkansas Workforce Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-301 et
17 seq., or the Arkansas Concurrent Challenge Scholarship Program, § 6-85-401 et
18 seq., the division shall first obtain review and approval from the
19 Legislative Council or, if the General Assembly is in session, the Joint
20 Budget Committee.
21
22 SECTION 14. DO NOT CODIFY. Transfer of funds.
23 (a) With the elimination of the Scholarship Shortfall Reserve Trust
24 Account, the twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) currently in the account
25 shall be first transferred and applied to the Office of the Arkansas
26 Lottery's Unrestricted Net Position account to reduce the deficit to zero
27 dollars ($0.00).
28 (b) Any funds remaining after the transfer under subsection (a) of
29 this section shall then be transferred to the Lottery Scholarship Trust
30 Account before December 31, 2025.
31 (c) The disbursement of funds under this section is a one-time
32 disbursement.
33
34 SECTION 15. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
35 General Assembly of the State of Arkansas that modifications to accounting
36 procedures for certain funds of the Office of the Arkansas Lottery are needed
7 03-18-2025 14:03:49 CRH049

As Engrossed: S2/25/25 S3/11/25 S3/18/25 SB232
1 to improve the function of the lottery; that improvements in efficiency for
2 the office are critical to ensure the success of the lottery in Arkansas; and
3 that this act should become effective at the beginning of the state's fiscal
4 year so that the office can implement these critical changes. Therefore, an
5 emergency is declared to exist, and this act being necessary for the
6 preservation of the public peace, health, and safety shall become effective
7 on July 1, 2025.
